cs.GT, cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.MA, cs.AI. 

The paper discusses the use of game theory for the coordination of multiagent systems, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics). The focus is on resource allocation problems, which could also fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The optimization of performance certificates and the use of linear programming suggest a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the coordination of multiple agents suggests a connection to cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). Finally, the use of utility functions and the goal of maximizing a welfare function suggest a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
